{
  "doc_id": "348",
  "text": "A fuzzy self-adaptation controller has favorable performance, strong robustness, and anti-jamming capability to time-varying nonlinear objects. Xu and Smith [CITATION_1] realized a depth control of AUVs by using the fuzzy self-adaptation controller and achieved relatively satisfying control effect. However, overshooting occurred in the early stage of the control. In addition, parameter adjustment of the PID [CITATION_2] or SMVS controller [CITATION_3] through the fuzzy algorithm improves the robustness and anti-jamming capability of the controller.",
